VALUES ('258f80de-a487-4ffa-ad97-7b96c9776fd7', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?', 'The senator''s reputation for honesty had taken years to build, but a single leaked memo nearly destroyed it overnight. To his supporters, the document seemed damning. Only later did investigators reveal that the memo had been altered before its release. With the forgery exposed, the senator''s standing was ______, and crowds that had jeered him weeks earlier now cheered.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"restored","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: with the forgery exposed and crowds cheering again, his standing returned to its former good state."},{"id":"B","text":"questioned","is_correct":false,"explanation":"His standing is no longer in doubt once the forgery is exposed and crowds cheer."},{"id":"C","text":"exaggerated","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Nothing suggests his reputation was overstated; it was wrongly damaged and then recovered."},{"id":"D","text":"abandoned","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This reverses the outcome; his standing recovers rather than being given up."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Find the clue
After the forgery was exposed, {{yellow:crowds that had jeered him weeks earlier now cheered}}.
Step 2 — Match the word
The reversal back to cheering shows his good standing was brought back, i.e., restored.
Distractor analysis:
- B: "Questioned" fits the moment of doubt, but that doubt ends once the forgery is revealed.
- C: "Exaggerated" has no support; the text never says his reputation was overblown.
- D: "Abandoned" contradicts the cheering crowds who return to his side.', 'After the lie is exposed and crowds cheer again, what happened to his reputation?', 'Craft and Structure', 'Words in Context', 'reading_writing', 'craft', 'WIC', NULL, 'medium', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
